name: kate
about: The King's argument was; that anything that had a head could be beheaded; and that you weren't to talk nonsense.

name: elizabeth
about: The Queen's argument was; that if something wasn't done about it in less than no time she' 'd have everybody executed; all round.

name: heinz
about: Alice could think of nothing else to say but  It belongs to the Duchess: you d better ask HER about it.

name: charles
about: When I'M a Duchess; she said to herself; (not in a very hopeful tone though);  I won't have any pepper in my kitchen AT ALL. Soup does very well without—Maybe it's always pepper that makes people hot-tempered;  she went on; very much pleased at having found out a new kind of rule;  and vinegar that makes them sour—and camomile that makes them bitter—and—and barley-sugar and such things that make children sweet-tempered.

name: sophie
q5: IT'S THE BEST THING IN THA WORLD

name: manel
about: Alice was very glad to find her in such a pleasant temper; and thought to herself that perhaps it was only the pepper that had made her so savage when they met in the kitchen.
